daemon: run: Usage: _build/macosx64/bin/infinit-daemon daemon run [OPTIONS]
Run daemon in the foreground

Options:
  -h, --help             show this help message
      --compatibility-version  compatibility version to force
  -s, --script           suppress extraneous human friendly messages and use JSON output
  -a, --as               user to run commands as (default: akim)
      --login-user       Login with selected user(s), of form 'user:password' (default: [])
      --mount            mount given volumes on startup, keep trying on error (default: [])
      --mount-root       Default root path for all mounts
      --default-network  Default network for volume creation
      --advertise-host   advertise extra endpoint using given host (default: [])
  -f, --fetch            fetch daemon from https://beyond.infinit.sh
  -p, --push             push daemon to https://beyond.infinit.sh
      --docker           Enable the Docker plugin
      --docker-user      System user to use for docker plugin
      --docker-home      Home directory to use for Docker user (default: /home/<docker-user>)
      --docker-socket-tcp  Use a TCP socket for docker plugin
      --docker-socket-port  TCP port to use to communicate with Docker, 0 for random (default: 0)
      --docker-socket-path  Path for plugin socket (default: /run/docker/plugins)
      --docker-descriptor-path  Path to add plugin descriptor (default: /usr/lib/docker/plugins)
      --docker-mount-substitute  [from:to|prefix] : Substitute 'from' to 'to' in advertised path (default: )
      --log-level        Log level to start volumes with (default: LOG)
      --log-path         Store volume logs in given path

